  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime of $25,000, a significant portion of which has already been restitutioned. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the sentencing guidelines for a first-time white-collar offense of this magnitude generally lean toward shorter custodial sentences or community-based corrections. The disruptive outburst from the courtroom spectator is irrelevant to the legal sentencing parameters and has been disregarded. An eight-month incarceration period is deemed sufficient to address the punitive and deterrent aspects of the law while allowing for rehabilitation.",
  "verdict": 8
}
